#to propagate changes to all .ini files, run master_to_inis.bash

#default gibbs settings are 100000000 iterations
#for testing, use 1000000
#default gibbs settings are .0003 particle weight
#i have set to .0006

-------------------

notes about gradient table formats:

1) dtk did not require inverting (flipping) gradient axes. dtk uses 'dtk.bvecs' and 'dtk.bvals'
2) mrtrix needs x-gradient inversion. mrtrix uses 'mrtrix_4XN.gradients'
3) gibbs needs y-gradient inversion. uses 'fsl.bvecs' and 'fsl.bvals'

-DG 2/25/2015
